doctype html
head
  title ED2TTS
  meta(charset='utf-8')
  meta(name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no')
  link(rel='stylesheet' href='https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/css/bootstrap.min.css' integrity='sha384-Vkoo8x4CGsO3+Hhxv8T/Q5PaXtkKtu6ug5TOeNV6gBiFeWPGFN9MuhOf23Q9Ifjh' crossorigin='anonymous')
body
  .navbar.bg-dark.navbar-expand-lg.navbar-dark
    a.navbar-brand(target="_blank" href="/") EncoreDecks to Tabletop Simulator (ED2TTS)
  .container
    .col-xl-12.py-md-3.pl-md-5.bd-content
      .jumbotron
        h1 Export your EncoreDecks to TTS
        p.lead ED2TTS creates a jpg of your deck in a format that is suitable for importing into Tabletop Simulator.
        img.img-fluid(src="/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp" alt="An example image created by ED2TTS. The image consists of 50 Weiss Schwarz cards arranged side by side in a 10x5 mosaic.")
      
      .section-usage
        h2 
          span.bd-content-title Usage
                
        p
          | To get started, choose a deck on 
          a(target="_blank" href='//encoredecks.com/') encoredecks.com
          |  that you would like to import into Tabletop Simulator.
        
          
        p
          | Copy & paste the URL to the deck below, and this website will give you a link which you can paste into Tabletop Simulator.
        
        
        .card.mb-3
          .card-body
            form
              .form-group
                label(for="deckUrl") EncoreDecks Deck URL
                input.form-control(type="text")
                small#deckUrlHelp.form-text.text-muted.mb-3 Example: https://www.encoredecks.com/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp
                
            .output-container
              #output-badge.badge.badge-primary.font-weight-bold
                a#output-link.lead(href=`//${domain}/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp` style="color: white;") #{domain}/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp

      .section-advanced-usage
      h2 
        span.bd-content-title Advanced Usage
      
      p
        | There is no need to visit this webpage to generate custom deck images; This webpage is simply a tutorial on how to use ED2TTS.
        | All you need to know to use ED2TTS is the domain name of this website and the EncoreDecks Deck ID, and you can skip having to paste the URL into the form above. 
        | The EncoreDecks Deck ID in the example below is #[strong ZT1ZXFQkp].
        
      p
        | For example, 
        
      p.font-italic https://www.encoredecks.com/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp
      p becomes 
      p.font-italic #[a(target="_blank" href=`//${domain}/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp`) #{domain}/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp].
      p You can manually type that URL into the custom deck creation menu in Tabletop Simulator and save time!
      
      img.img-fluid.mb-3(src="/custom-deck-example.jpg" style="width: 50%")

      p
        | Deck images generated by ED2TTS are stored in the cloud and cached, which means there are no extra steps in Tabletop Simulator for using your decks in Multiplayer games!


      h2 
        span.bd-content-title Future Improvements
      ul
        li hi-res card images.
        
      h2 
        span.bd-content-title Author
      p Chris Grimmett #[a(href="mailto:chris@grimtech.net") chris@grimtech.net]

  script(src='https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.4.1.slim.min.js' integrity='sha384-J6qa4849blE2+poT4WnyKhv5vZF5SrPo0iEjwBvKU7imGFAV0wwj1yYfoRSJoZ+n' crossorigin='anonymous')
  script(src='https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/popper.js@1.16.0/dist/umd/popper.min.js' integrity='sha384-Q6E9RHvbIyZFJoft+2mJbHaEWldlvI9IOYy5n3zV9zzTtmI3UksdQRVvoxMfooAo' crossorigin='anonymous')
